    <Paragraph>This example shows how to get all Window objects in an application.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>Every instantiated <Run FontWeight="Bold">Window</Run>
 object, whether visible or not, is automatically added to a collection of window references that is managed by Application, and exposed from Windows.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>You can enumerate <Run FontWeight="Bold">Windows</Run>
 to get all instantiated windows using the following code:
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>C# </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>foreach( Window window in Application.Current.Windows ) { Console.WriteLine(window.Title); 
} </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

